Description: Photograph (black and white); a view of Bab Zuweila (a medieval gate); five men crouched in a circle on a street in the foreground; Cairo, Egypt. Gelatin silver print
Curator's comments: Related image: The National Library of Australia has a similar image: nla.pic-an23815842.
Acquisition notes: Photos accompanied by a note that reads: "Photographs bought at Sotheby's Belgravia sale of 21 March 1980, lot 381: 'A group of topographical and ethnographical photographs, by Captain Frank Hurley, taken on the occasion of an exploratory trip around the islands of the South Pacific, comprising a total of forty-two Photographs including studies of natives, native rituals and settlements and landscapes, Bromide Prints, various sizes, early 20th century.' See Capt. Frank Hurley, Pearls and Savages: adventures in the air, on land and sea - in New Guinea. G.P.P. Putnam's sons, New York, London, 1924
